# 💰 FinTrack — Personal Finance & Budget Tracker

A full-stack PERN application built with **PostgreSQL (Supabase)**, **Express.js**, **React**, and **Node.js**. Features income/expense tracking, category-based budgets with visual progress alerts, and an analytics dashboard powered by Recharts.

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
fintrack/
├── server/                    # Express.js REST API
│   ├── config/
│   │   └── supabase.js        # Supabase service-role client
│   ├── controllers/           # Route handlers (thin layer)
│   ├── services/              # Business logic & DB queries
│   ├── routes/                # Express routers
│   ├── middleware/
│   │   ├── authenticate.js    # JWT verification
│   │   └── errorHandler.js    # Global error handler
│   ├── validators/            # Request body validation
│   └── index.js               # Server entry point
│
├── client/                    # React + Vite frontend
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── context/
│   │   │   └── AuthContext.jsx
│   │   ├── services/
│   │   │   └── api.js         # Centralised fetch wrapper
│   │   ├── components/
│   │   │   ├── Layout.jsx
│   │   │   ├── ProtectedRoute.jsx
│   │   │   ├── StatCard.jsx
│   │   │   ├── BudgetProgressBar.jsx
│   │   │   ├── RecentTransactions.jsx
│   │   │   └── TransactionForm.jsx
│   │   ├── pages/
│   │   │   ├── Dashboard.jsx
│   │   │   ├── Transactions.jsx
│   │   │   ├── Budgets.jsx
│   │   │   ├── Login.jsx
│   │   │   └── Register.jsx
│   │   └── App.jsx
│   └── index.html
│
└── supabase_schema.sql        # Full DB schema with RLS policies
```

---

## 🗄️ Database Setup (Supabase)

1. Create a free project at [supabase.com](https://supabase.com).
2. Go to **SQL Editor** and paste the contents of `supabase_schema.sql`.
3. Run the script — this creates all tables, enums, RLS policies, and the `budget_progress` view.

---

## ⚙️ Environment Variables

### Server (`server/.env`)

```env
PORT=5000
CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:5173

# From Supabase → Project Settings → API
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key
```

### Client (`client/.env`)

```env
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api
```

---

## 🚀 Installation & Running

### Prerequisites

- Node.js >= 18
- npm >= 9

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/fintrack.git
cd fintrack
```

### 2. Install server dependencies

```bash
cd server
npm install
```

### 3. Install client dependencies

```bash
cd ../client
npm install
```

### 4. Start the backend

```bash
# from /server
npm run dev
```

### 5. Start the frontend

```bash
# from /client
npm run dev
```

Open [http://localhost:5173](http://localhost:5173) in your browser.

---

## 📦 Key Dependencies

| Layer    | Package                  | Purpose                       |
|----------|--------------------------|-------------------------------|
| Backend  | `express`                | HTTP server & routing         |
| Backend  | `@supabase/supabase-js`  | DB client & Auth verification |
| Backend  | `helmet`, `cors`         | Security headers              |
| Backend  | `morgan`                 | HTTP request logging          |
| Frontend | `react-router-dom`       | Client-side routing           |
| Frontend | `recharts`               | Charts (Bar, Pie)             |
| Frontend | `tailwindcss`            | Utility-first styling         |

---

## 🔐 Auth Flow

1. User registers or logs in via `POST /api/auth/register|login`.
2. The backend calls Supabase Auth and returns a JWT `access_token`.
3. The React client stores the token in `localStorage` and sends it as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` on all protected requests.
4. The `authenticate` middleware validates the token with Supabase on every protected route.

---

## 📊 Budget Progress Logic

```
progress_pct = (SUM of expenses in category this month / budget amount) × 100
```

- **Green** bar: progress < 75 %  
- **Amber** bar: progress 75–100 %  
- **Red** bar + warning text: progress > 100 % (over budget)

This is computed server-side in the `budget_progress` SQL view and returned by `GET /api/budgets/progress`.

---

## 🧪 API Endpoints

| Method | Path                        | Description                          |
|--------|-----------------------------|--------------------------------------|
| POST   | `/api/auth/register`        | Register new user                    |
| POST   | `/api/auth/login`           | Login, returns JWT                   |
| GET    | `/api/transactions`         | List transactions (filterable)       |
| POST   | `/api/transactions`         | Create transaction                   |
| PUT    | `/api/transactions/:id`     | Update transaction                   |
| DELETE | `/api/transactions/:id`     | Delete transaction                   |
| GET    | `/api/budgets`              | List budgets                         |
| GET    | `/api/budgets/progress`     | Budget progress with spent amounts   |
| POST   | `/api/budgets`              | Create budget                        |
| GET    | `/api/categories`           | List user's categories               |
| POST   | `/api/categories`           | Create category                      |